cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a wireless network and scheduling of links, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the optimization of link rates, which is a topic of interest in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an approach to solve the minimum-time scheduling problem, which can be seen as a control problem. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper mentions the problem of minimum-time scheduling being NP-hard, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper deals with a network of transmitters and receivers, which can be seen as a multiagent system.
